in his description of alexanderi , its two syntypes from 38° 30´S and 56° W in the South Atlantic are small, with wing 600 mm and culmen 152–160 mm , and match members of the Wandering Albatross complex breeding on those islands. The name
dabbenena
was originally introduced conditionally (and unavailably) by Mathews (1929) , to replace alexanderi Dabbene if the prospective prior homonym
Thalassogeron chrysostoma alexanderi Mathews, 1916
was ever included in the genus
Diomedea
